s=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> Can an epic level player enlighten me on this.... are the other epics actually more DIFFICULT.... tougher fights more complicated... o r are they just more and longer camps? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhinterdir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HinterDir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 9:30:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/osllonewolf/Lonewolf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> or look at it that way:<br>all guilds usualy start out with the Rogue's Epics because it gives them the Damage Output to even bother with some of the mobs that are required for all the others..<br><br>and Prenn, i don't recall the monk epic beeing very hard either <p><hr><p align="center"><ahref="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7428"><fontcolor="#008080" size="4" face="Castellar"><strong>Hinterdir</strong></font></a></p><p align="center"><font color="#008080" size="4" face="Castellar">Assassin</font></p><p align="center"><font color="#008080" size="2" face="Castellar">CounsilMember of</font><font color="#008080" face="Castellar"> </font><ahref="http://www.wolfsclan-eq.de"><font color="#008080" size="4"face="Castellar"><strong>Wolfsclan</strong></font></a><fontcolor="#008080" face="Castellar"> </font><font color="#008080"size="2" face="Castellar">on Solusek Ro</font></p><p align="center"><font color="#008080" size="2" face="Castellar">SolusekRo Ring Warden</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeddo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keddo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 9:34:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> A weeks time is a general statement. For some people that play 16 hours a day that's like 95 hours of game play. Surely a person who has played EQ long enough to get a war epic, has the resources(guild, friends, robes stashed from long ago) to get the rogue epic in that time. So before judging someone and saying that they don't deserve something because it only took them X amount of time, take into consideration that maybe they have been playing for 2+ years and know how to play the game(as in all classes). <br>While i can understand jealousy and envy in this, some people just need to come down off their pedastals and move on. Just because it took you 3 months or whatever to get your epic, doesn't mean that everyone should. <p><a href = http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8121>Keddo 60 High Priest</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unotwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>notwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 10:05:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> No most other epics are not &quot;harder.&quot;  They require more camping, some less common pieces, etc etc.  They have bigger bottle necks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaowyth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caowyth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 10:45:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> If you had to do the Vilnius quests to move forward with the epic, I wouldn't consider it to be too easy.<br><br>But you don't.<br><br>Cao<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umeddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meddik</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.aodoctors.org/Cross.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 11:07:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> Well, in general, the most difficult part IS the bottleneck.<br><br>Heck, If you made the Ragefire encounter 10x as difficult (in terms of damage, etc.), but removed the bottleneck, I'd bet that every cleric would rejoice.<br><br>Nobody minds a tough, overwhelmingly difficult fight. The problem for most is waiting in line for the fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 11:30:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/housecalls/nextlevel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> I think something that most people don't consider when comparing the epic quests are WHO does the epic benefit most?  Our RB really just helps the rogue do her job better.  I can't lend those benefits to anyone else in my group or guild.  Just me.  Even the monk gloves give a haste that stacks better than ours.  The click-stick, as an example, can benefit ANYONE the cleric looks at.  Yes, that quest SHOULD be much harder. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umeddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meddik</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.aodoctors.org/Cross.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 11:37:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> Harder? Yes indeed.<br><br>More Bottlenecked? No. Not at all.<br><br>I know, I disagree with VI's view of "Time spend sitting on your arse waiting for your turn at a spawn = risk in the risk/reward ratio". But, I think their measurement is silly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unotwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>notwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 12:15:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> I disagree Lanella.  Both help self and guild/friends.<br><br>A Rogue w/o ragebringer is not worth as much on a raid as a rogue with.  It's not as direct an effect on the individual player as a 56 rez from the Cleric epic, but the weapon is still a huge boon to the people the rogue fights with.<br><br>Alternatively, the non-cleric epic can do the same rezzes at 56+ (which most epic clerics are), and a *slightly* less effective rez pre-56.  The epic makes it just makes it more mana efficient (ie mana free).  This aids the cleric to do his/her job better... most specificly helps in getting rezzes done more quickly after a wipeout. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugyorg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gyorg</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 2:11:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~gyorg/orion.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></