an class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> The general is the only part of the rogue epic that requires more then a single group.<br><br>Yes, the story is great. Yes, pickpocketting the GMs and sneaking naked through hate are very 'roguely' things to do. I wish all epics tested class-particular skills like that. In fact, it's the best designed quest. It's the one that relies least on irritating camping, and I wish all the others were so well done.<br><br>That doesn't change the fact that it's pathetically easy. It could stand to be twice as long for the rewards. You can pick the notes, get the book, and kill renux in a day. Compare the necro epic, which is a near-useless toy, with the Freebringer, which is godly until the endgame and every rogue you see 55+ has. Now, which one is ungodly difficult and which one is easy?<br><br>Once again, I'm not saying it's a crappy quest, or needs to be nerfed. It's just pathetically easy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyalum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yalum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 5:07:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> However, you can't do the monk epic 11 freaking times in a couple of hours like people do the general.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You can kill Eejag 11 times in a couple hours.  Does that get you your shiny new gloves?  Nope, but neither does killing General usually result in a new poker.<br><br>People look at the monk epic, see three fights you can do with two groups or less, and say &quot;Wow, the monk epic is easy&quot;.  They miss all the robe crap you have to do beforehand.  Likewise, people look at rogue epic, see a moderately hard fight that can be chain spawned, and say &quot;Wow, the rogue epic is easy&quot;.  They miss all the robe crap we have to do afterwards.<br><br>Even the &quot;easy&quot; epics have their annoying bottlenecks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaowyth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caowyth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 5:18:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4517.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats on your Freebringer!!</span><hr size=1> All the robe crap?<br><br>Oracle Robe, SMR, Ishva can all be bought.<br><br>Kedge robe has two drops in the game, and can also be multi'd.<br><br>Plus there's a small chance every General that you can skip the robes.<br><br>Right, thats comparable.<br><br>If the rogues had to do every step of Vilnius's quest before they moved on, then you could say the back-questing was comparable to a monk.<br><br>Cao <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upandajoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PandaJoe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://forums.off-topic.net/images/smilies/bash.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 6:01:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafeh